**Abstract:**
Essay titled "After Truth" opening with quotations from McInerny, Marshall on Lindbeck, and examining what remains after abandoning the contemplative paradigm of truth. Argues practical convictions guide action without being "pictures corresponding to reality." Distinguishes own position from Lindbeck's intrasystematic truth by frankly denying ontological truth. Critiques Caputo's deconstructionism for remaining within contemplative paradigm despite claims to the contrary.

**AI Recommendation:** Major theoretical essay on post-foundationalist faith; variant of 98-FEB-1.

